  - openai-cookbook
abstract: |
  An adversarially-reviewed audit of OpenAI's Macro Evals for Agentic Systems
  cookbook. Five hypotheses pre-registered against synthetic agent traces;
  most refuted by their own thresholds. The 60-named-expert review identified
  document construction as the load-bearing design decision in the cookbook's
  pipeline template, and the article makes a structural argument for why that
  decision propagates downstream.
